tmnxBsxNgMIBModule.name: tmnxBsxNgMIBModule

revisions.description: Rev 9.0 01 Feb 2011 00:00 9.0 release of the TIMETRA-BSX-NG-MIB.
Rev 7.0 03 Dec 2008 00:00 7.0 release of the TIMETRA-BSX-NG-MIB.

tmnxBsxNgMIBModule.description: This document is the SNMP MIB module to manage and provision the Application Assurance capability of the Alcatel-Lucent SROS device. Copyright (c) 2010-2012 Alcatel-Lucent. All rights reserved. Reproduction of this document is authorized on the condition that the foregoing copyright notice is included. This SNMP MIB module (Specification) embodies Alcatel-Lucent's proprietary intellectual property. Alcatel-Lucent retains all title and ownership in the Specification, including any revisions. Alcatel-Lucent grants all interested parties a non-exclusive license to use and distribute an unmodified copy of this Specification in connection with management of Alcatel-Lucent products, and without fee, provided this copyright notice and license appear on all copies. TmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex.name: TmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex
TmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex.description: TmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex is an index of a group of BSX MDAs.

TmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndexOrZero.name: TmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndexOrZero
TmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndexOrZero.description: TmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndexOrZero is an index of a group of BSX MDAs. The value of zero indicates that no BSX MDA group is specified.

TmnxBsxAaGrpPartIndex.name: TmnxBsxAaGrpPartIndex
TmnxBsxAaGrpPartIndex.description: TmnxBsxAaGrpPartIndex is an index of an Application Assurance partition within an Application Assurance group, and is a unique 32-bit number encoded as follows. | 32 25 | 24 9 | 8 1 | +---------+---------+----------+ | 0 | partidx | groupidx| Partition Index +---------+---------+----------+ - groupidx represents a group of ISA MDAs and has a valid range from 1..255. The corresponding TmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex must already exist in the tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTable. - partidx represents a partition within a group and has a valid range from 0..65535. A partition index of '0' represents group wide information.

TmnxBsxFailToMode.name: TmnxBsxFailToMode
TmnxBsxFailToMode.description: TmnxBsxFailToMode specifies how traffic is handled when there are no available ISA-AA cards to handle the traffic.

TmnxBsxPolicyVersion.name: TmnxBsxPolicyVersion
TmnxBsxPolicyVersion.description: TmnxBsxPolicyVersion specifies either the administrative or the operational version of the policy. Configuration changes can only be made to the administrative version of the policy. The operational copy is updated when a 'commit' operation is done.

TmnxBsxDirection.name: TmnxBsxDirection
TmnxBsxDirection.description: TmnxBsxDirection specifies either the subscriber to network 'sub2net' or the network to subscriber direction 'net2sub' or that the policy is to apply to 'both'.

TmnxBsxPolicerType.name: TmnxBsxPolicerType
TmnxBsxPolicerType.description: TmnxBsxPolicerType specifies whether the policer is a bandwidth, flow rate, or a flow count policer in addition to the number of buckets used by the policer.

TmnxBsxGranularity.name: TmnxBsxGranularity
TmnxBsxGranularity.description: TmnxBsxGranularity specifies either 'system' to create one policer instance per system or 'subscriber' to create one policer instance per subscriber.

TmnxBsxPolicerAction.name: TmnxBsxPolicerAction
TmnxBsxPolicerAction.description: TmnxBsxPolicerAction specifies either 'permitDeny' to permit or deny packets or 'priorityMark' to mark to in or out of profile based on the outcome of the policer.

TmnxBsxBurstSize.name: TmnxBsxBurstSize
TmnxBsxBurstSize.description: The amount of burst capacity (in kbytes) assigned to a policer.

TmnxBsxOperator.name: TmnxBsxOperator
TmnxBsxOperator.description: TmnxBsxOperator specifies the type of comparison operator to perform on another associated member of the row of the table.

TmnxBsxMdaRole.name: TmnxBsxMdaRole
TmnxBsxMdaRole.description: TmnxBsxMdaRole specifies the configured role of an ISA-AA MDA. An MDA may take on the role of: primary (0) - configured within an ISA-AA group as a primary backup (1) - configured within an ISA-AA group as a backup Multiple primary ISA-AA MDAs can be configured in an ISA-AA group, but only one backup.

TmnxBsxMdaActivityState.name: TmnxBsxMdaActivityState
TmnxBsxMdaActivityState.description: TmnxBsxMdaActivityState specifies the working state of an ISA-AA MDA in a group. The Activity state may be one of: unavailable (0) - is not available to provide service active (1) - is online and providing service standby (2) - is online, but not providing service

TmnxBsxAaSubscriberType.name: TmnxBsxAaSubscriberType
TmnxBsxAaSubscriberType.description: A value that represents a type (and thereby the format) of a TmnxBsxAaSubscriber. The value can be one of the following: unknown (0) - An unknown subscriber type is specified. esm (1) - Enhanced Subscriber Management identity is specified. This indicates that the format of the TmnxBsxAaSubscriber is the Enhanced Subscriber Management Subscriber as specified in the TIMETRA-SUBSCRIBER-MGMT-MIB in tmnxSubInfoSubIdent in the tmnxSubscriberInfoTable. The value of the TmnxBsxAaSubscriber is a NON IMPLIED String of type TNamedItem. sap (2) - A Service Access Point (SAP) is specified. This indicates that the format of the TmnxBsxAaSubscriber is an OCTET string containing the Service Access Point (SAP) subscriber as specified in the TIMETRA-SAP-MIB including the sapPortId and sapEncapValue. Octets Contents 1-4 sapPortId (unsigned integer), 5-8 sapEncapValue (unsigned integer) spokeSdp (3) - A spoke SDP binding is specified. This indicates that the format of the TmnxBsxAaSubscriber is an OCTET string containing the spoke SDP Binding Id as specified in the TIMETRA-SDP-MIB in sdpBindId in the sdpBindTable. transit (4) - A Transit subscriber is specified. This indicates that the format of the TmnxBsxAaSubscriber is an OCTET string containing the transit subscriber name. mobile (5) - A mobile subscriber is specified. This indicates that the format of the TmnxBsxAaSubscriber is an OCTET string containing the mobile subscriber name. The value of the TmnxBsxAaSubscriber is a NON IMPLIED String of type TNamedItem.

TmnxBsxAaSubscriber.name: TmnxBsxAaSubscriber
TmnxBsxAaSubscriber.description: Denotes a generic Application Assurance Subscriber. An TmnxBsxAaSubscriber value is always interpreted within the context of an TmnxBsxAaSubscriberType value. Every usage of the TmnxBsxAaSubscriber textual convention is required to specify the TmnxBsxAaSubscriberType object that provides the context. The value of an TmnxBsxAaSubscriber object must always be consistent with the value of the associated TmnxBsxAaSubscriberType object. Attempts to set an TmnxBsxAaSubscriber object to a value inconsistent with the associated TmnxBsxAaSubscriberType will fail with an inconsistentValue error.

TmnxBsxStatAaAcctCfgType.name: TmnxBsxStatAaAcctCfgType
TmnxBsxStatAaAcctCfgType.description: Represents all of the possible statistics accounting types that can be configured within an Application Assurance group and partition. The various types are: unknown - unknown statistics type protocol - system wide protocol stats application - system wide application stats app-group - system wide app-group stats aa-sub - subscriber specific stats aa-sub-study-protocol - special study protocol subscriber stats aa-sub-study-application - special study app subscriber stats

TmnxBsxAaStatType.name: TmnxBsxAaStatType
TmnxBsxAaStatType.description: Represents the various kinds of statistics objects used in Application Assurance. The various types are: unknown - unknown protocol - protocol based statistics application - application based statistics app-group - application group based statistics chargingGroup - charging group based statistics

TmnxBsxAaStatExportMethod.name: TmnxBsxAaStatExportMethod
TmnxBsxAaStatExportMethod.description: Represents the method to use to export statistics in Application Assurance. The various methods are: accountingPolicy - use the accounting policy radiusAccountingPolicy - use the RADIUS accounting policy

TmnxBsxExprSubStringIndex.name: TmnxBsxExprSubStringIndex
TmnxBsxExprSubStringIndex.description: TmnxBsxExprSubStringIndex is an index of a list of expression substrings.

TmnxBsxExprSubStringType.name: TmnxBsxExprSubStringType
TmnxBsxExprSubStringType.description: A value that represents a type (and thereby the expression substring) of a TmnxBsxExprSubString. The various types are: none - no substring httpHost - HTTP host substring httpUri - HTTP URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) substring httpReferrer - HTTP referrer substring sipUa - SIP UA (User Agent) substring sipUri - SIP URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) substring sipMt - SIP RTP Media Type substring citrixApp - Citrix application substring httpUserAgent - HTTP User Agent substring h323ProductId - H323 Product Id substring tlsCsOrgName - TLS Certificate Subject Organization Name substring tlsCsCommonName - TLS Certificate Subject Common Name substring

TmnxBsxExprSubString.name: TmnxBsxExprSubString
TmnxBsxExprSubString.description: Denotes a printable ASCII substring used as input to an application assurance filter match criteria object. The following syntax is permitted within the substring to define the pattern match criteria: ^<substring>* - matches when <substring> is at the beginning of the object. *<substring>* - matches when <substring> is at any place within the object. *<substring>$ - matches when <substring> is at the end of the object. ^<substring>$ - matches when <substring> is the entire object. Rules for <substring> characters: --------------------------------- - <substring> must contain printable ASCII characters. - <substring> must not contain the 'double quote' character or the ' ' (space) character on its own. - <substring> match is case sensitive. - <substring> must not include any Regular Expression meta-characters. - The '\' character is used as an ESCAPE sequence. - the following ESCAPE sequences are permitted within the <substring>: character to match <substring> input ------------------ ------------------ \ \\ Hexidecimal Octet YY \xYY Note: A <substring> that uses the '\' (backslash) ESCAPE character which is not followed by a '\' or '\x' and a 2-digit hex octet is not valid.

TmnxBsxFirstPacketPolicy.name: TmnxBsxFirstPacketPolicy
TmnxBsxFirstPacketPolicy.description: TmnxBsxFirstPacketPolicy specifies the policy to apply to the first packet within a flow. The First Packet Policy may be one of: none (0) - there is no policy to apply first-packet-trusted (1) - the first packet is trusted first-packet-validate (2) - the first packet is validated

TmnxBsxActionStatus.name: TmnxBsxActionStatus
TmnxBsxActionStatus.description: TmnxBsxActionStatus specifies the status of an ISA-AA action. The status may be one of: none (0) - no action start (1) - action has started stop (2) - action has stopped

TmnxBsxAdminCtrl.name: TmnxBsxAdminCtrl
TmnxBsxAdminCtrl.description: TmnxBsxAdminCtrl specifies the copying and editing of tmnxBsxPolicyObjs tables from one instance of a policy version to another. The admin control may be one of: none (1) - no policies being edited initialize (2) - policies being edited commit (3) - policies commited

TmnxBsxCustProtExprSubString.name: TmnxBsxCustProtExprSubString
TmnxBsxCustProtExprSubString.description: Denotes a printable ASCII substring used as input to an application assurance custom protocol match criteria object. Rules for <substring> characters: --------------------------------- - <substring> must contain printable ASCII characters. - <substring> must not contain the 'double quote' character or the ' ' (space) character on its own. - <substring> match is case sensitive. - <substring> must not include any Regular Expression meta-characters. - The '\' character is used as an ESCAPE sequence. - the following ESCAPE sequences are permitted within the <substring>: character to match <substring> input ------------------ ------------------ \ \\ Hexidecimal Octet YY \xYY Note: A <substring> that uses the '\' (backslash) ESCAPE character which is not followed by a '\' or '\x' and a 2-digit hex octet is not valid.

TmnxBsxProtocolDirection.name: TmnxBsxProtocolDirection
TmnxBsxProtocolDirection.description: TmnxBsxProtocolDirection specifies the direction to match for a protocol. The protocol direction may be one of: none (0) - no direction specified client2server (1) - client to server direction server2client (2) - server to client direction any (3) - any direction

TmnxBsxLoadBalanceStatus.name: TmnxBsxLoadBalanceStatus
TmnxBsxLoadBalanceStatus.description: TmnxBsxLoadBalanceStatus specifies the status of a load-balance operation in an ISA-AA group. The status may be one of: balancing (0) - load-balance in progress complete (1) - load-balance completed

TmnxBsxCflowdExpType.name: TmnxBsxCflowdExpType
TmnxBsxCflowdExpType.description: Represents the various kinds of statistics which can be exported using Cflowd in Application Assurance. The various types are: none - no statistics exported volume - volume statistics tcpPerformance - TCP performance statistics rtpPerformance - RTP performance statistics

TmnxBsxCflowdPerfMeasType.name: TmnxBsxCflowdPerfMeasType
TmnxBsxCflowdPerfMeasType.description: Represents the various kinds of performance measurement types which can be exported using Cflowd in Application Assurance. The various types are: none - no measurement type specified tcp - tcp performance measurements rtp - realtime transport protocol performance measurements

TmnxBsxAaSubStatsInterval.name: TmnxBsxAaSubStatsInterval
TmnxBsxAaSubStatsInterval.description: Represents the various types of statistics intervals for Application Assurance subscribers. The various types are: unknown - specifies an unknown statistics interval realtime - specifies that the statistics retrieved include the sum of the statistics from the previous collection windows, the statistics for any closed flows since the last collection window, and the statistics accumulated from any currently open flows. snapshot - specifies that the statistics retrieved include the sum of the statistics from the previous collection windows, and the statistics for any closed flows since the last collection window.

TmnxBsxAaSubAcctLossReason.name: TmnxBsxAaSubAcctLossReason
TmnxBsxAaSubAcctLossReason.description: Represents the reason for a loss of Application Assurance subscriber accounting statistics. The various reasons are: noLoss - no accounting statistics have been lost. acctInvlExpiry - accounting interval has expired

TmnxBsxAaSubAsoValDerivedFrom.name: TmnxBsxAaSubAsoValDerivedFrom
TmnxBsxAaSubAsoValDerivedFrom.description: TmnxBsxAaSubAsoValDerivedFrom specifies from where the characteristic value is being derived from for the Application Assurance subscriber. The characteristic value can be derived from Application Service Option (ASO) defaults, application profiles, or policy-overrides.

TmnxBsxAaSubPolicerResStatus.name: TmnxBsxAaSubPolicerResStatus
TmnxBsxAaSubPolicerResStatus.description: TmnxBsxAaSubPolicerResStatus specifies the status of policer resources being applied to an Application Assurance subscriber. The status may be one of: none (0) okay (1) - policer resources are not exceeded unknown (2) - policer resources are unknown exceeded (3) - policer resources are exceeded

TmnxBsxStatIsaAaCfgType.name: TmnxBsxStatIsaAaCfgType
TmnxBsxStatIsaAaCfgType.description: Represents all of the possible statistics accounting types that can be configured at the ISA-AA group level. The various types are: unknown - unknown statistics type aaPerformance - AA performance statistics

TmnxBsxTransitSubOrigin.name: TmnxBsxTransitSubOrigin
TmnxBsxTransitSubOrigin.description: Represents the possible ways in which the transit AA subscriber was created. The various origins of a transit subscriber are: static - statically provisioned dhcp - dynamically learned via DHCP radius - dynamically learned via RADIUS autoSeenIp - automatically created via Seen IP A transit subscriber may have more than one origin. The absence of any bits indicates a subscriber of unknown origin.

TmnxBsxTListAttribType.name: TmnxBsxTListAttribType
TmnxBsxTListAttribType.description: Represents the different types of value a tagged list attribute can possess. The various types of values are: none(0) - no value uint(1) - an unsigned integer string(2) - a displayable string

TmnxBsxTListAttribValue.name: TmnxBsxTListAttribValue
TmnxBsxTListAttribValue.description: Represents the different values of a tagged list attribute. A TmnxBsxTListAttribValue is always interpreted within the context of a TmnxBsxTListAttribType. Every usage of TmnxBsxTListAttribValue is required to specify the TmnxBsxTListAttribType that provides that context. If the TmnxBsxTListAttribType is 'uint(1)' then the numerical value is stored in the first 4 bytes of the octet string as a 32-bit value. If the TmnxBsxTListAttribType is a 'string(2)' then string is packed into TmnxBsxTListAttribValue.

TmnxBsxAqpHttpRedirFlowType.name: TmnxBsxAqpHttpRedirFlowType
TmnxBsxAqpHttpRedirFlowType.description: Represents the different types of flows that can be redirected. The different types of flows are: none(0) - no flows droppedFlows(1) - dropped flows

TmnxBsxAarpInstState.name: TmnxBsxAarpInstState
TmnxBsxAarpInstState.description: Represents the different states of an Application Assurance Redundancy Protocol (AARP) instance performing asymmetry removal. Asymmetry refers to a situation where the two directions of traffic for a specific flow take different paths through the network. Asymmetry removal ensures that packets for each flow and all flows for each subscriber are processed by the same ISA-AA. The states are: standAlone(0) - AARP instance is handling AA independently from the peer. Traffic asymmetry is not removed. Caused by a configuration problem or failure in asymmetry removal resources. remote(1) - AARP instance is sending all AA traffic to the remote peer. Traffic asymmetry is removed. Locally unable to perform AA and act as a backup due to failure of a local AA-ISA. master(2) - AARP instance is handling AA locally for local traffic and remote traffic from the peer. Traffic asymmetry is removed. backup(3) - AARP instance is sending all AA traffic to the remote peer. Traffic asymmetry is removed. Locally ready to take over.

TmnxBsxAarpInstOperFlags.name: TmnxBsxAarpInstOperFlags
TmnxBsxAarpInstOperFlags.description: TmnxBsxAarpInstOperFlags represents the different conditions that affect the operating status of an AARP instance. The bit values are: adminDown(0) - AARP instance is administratively down. noSubConfigd(1) - no 'dualHomed(2)' subscriber reference configured against the AARP instance. peerDown(2) - no communication with peer AARP instance. peerAarpDown(3) - MC-CTL link is up, but AARP layer protocol interaction with peer AARP instance is not established. subTypeMismatch(4) - mismatch detected in the subscriber types between peer AARP instances. subDown(5) - 'dualHomed(2)' subscriber reference is operationally down. shuntsDown(6) - one of the shunts referenced by the AARP instance is down. divertCapDown(7) - divert to AA not possible - divert capability is down. appProfNoDivert(8) - app-profile used by the 'dualHomed(2)' subscriber reference has 'no divert' set. subSidePipeMismatch(9) - mismatch detected in the subscriber-side pipe between AARP instances. subSideIfMismatch(10) - mismatch detected in the subscriber-side interface between peer AARP instances. netSidePipeMistmatch(11) - mismatch detected in the network-side pipe between AARP instances. netSideIfMismatch(12) - mismatch detected in in the network- side interface between peer AARP instances. unsupportedIoms(13) - IOMs which do not support AARP have been detected.

TmnxBsxAarpCommand.name: TmnxBsxAarpCommand
TmnxBsxAarpCommand.description: TmnxBsxAarpCommand represents the different commands that can be performed on an AARP instance. The command values are: noCmd (0) - 'noCmd(0)' is returned by a read request when no control command has been written to the object since initialization. 'noCmd(0)' should not be used as a value for a write operation - the write operation will fail. forceEvaluate (1) - the command triggers a re-evaluation of the preferred AARP instance.

TmnxBsxAarpServPointRole.name: TmnxBsxAarpServPointRole
TmnxBsxAarpServPointRole.description: TmnxBsxAarpServPointRole represents the different roles that an AARP instance service point can assume. The roles of service points are: none (0) - no role. dualHomed (1) - a service point into the dual homed network being protected by AARP. pipeShuntSub (2) - subscriber side pipe shunt. pipeShuntNet (3) - network side pipe shunt. interfaceShuntSub (4) - subscriber side interface shunt. interfaceShuntNet (5) - network side interface shunt.

TmnxBsxAarpServPointType.name: TmnxBsxAarpServPointType
TmnxBsxAarpServPointType.description: TmnxBsxAarpServPointType represents the different types (and thereby the different formats) of TmnxBsxAarpServPoint (an AARP instance service point). The types of service points are: unknown (0) - unknown. sap (1) - A Service Access Point (SAP) is specified. This indicates that the format of the TmnxBsxAarpServPoint is an OCTET STRING containing the Service Access Point (SAP) as specified in the TIMETRA-SAP-MIB including the sapPortId and sapEncapValue. Octets Contents 1-4 sapPortId (unsigned integer), 5-8 sapEncapValue (unsigned integer) spokeSdp (2) - A spoke SDP binding is specified. This indicates that the format of the TmnxBsxAarpServPoint is an OCTET STRING containing the spoke SDP Binding Id as specified in the TIMETRA-SDP-MIB in sdpBindId in the sdpBindTable.

TmnxBsxAarpServPoint.name: TmnxBsxAarpServPoint
TmnxBsxAarpServPoint.description: TmnxBsxAarpServPoint represents a generic AARP instance service point. An TmnxBsxAarpServPoint value is always interpreted within the context of an TmnxBsxAarpServPointType value. Every usage of the TmnxBsxAarpServPoint textual convention is required to specify the TmnxBsxAarpServPointType object that provides the context. The value of an TmnxBsxAarpServPoint object must always be consistent with the value of the associated TmnxBsxAarpServPointType object. Attempts to set an TmnxBsxAarpServPoint object to a value inconsistent with the associated TmnxBsxAarpServPointType will fail with an inconsistentValue error.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpLastChangeTime.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpLastChangeTime
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpLastChangeTime.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpLastChangeTime indicates the last time a successful set was performed on the tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTable.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcLastChangeTime.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcLastChangeTime
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcLastChangeTime.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcLastChangeTime indicates the last time a successful set was performed on the tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcTable.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpMdaLastChangeTime.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpMdaLastChangeTime
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpMdaLastChangeTime.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpMdaLastChangeTime indicates the last time a successful set was performed on the tmnxBsxGrpMdaTable.

tmnxBsxAaGrpPartLastChangeTime.name: tmnxBsxAaGrpPartLastChangeTime
tmnxBsxAaGrpPartLastChangeTime.description: The value of tmnxBsxAaGrpPartLastChangeTime indicates the last time a successful set was performed on the tmnxBsxAaGrpPartTable.

tmnxBsxAaWap1xLastChangeTime.name: tmnxBsxAaWap1xLastChangeTime
tmnxBsxAaWap1xLastChangeTime.description: The value of tmnxBsxAaWap1xLastChangeTime indicates the last time a successful set was performed on the tmnxBsxAaWap1xTable.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTable.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTable
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTable.description: The tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTable contains an entry for each BSX MDA Group in the system.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpEntry.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpEntry
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpEntry.description: Each tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpEntry indicates a BSX MDA group in the system.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex
tmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex indicates the group number of this group of BSX MDAs.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpRowStatus.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpRowStatus
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpRowStatus specifies the row status. It allows entries to be created and deleted in the tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTable. To delete an entry, all references to this ISA-AA group in all policy and transit policy tables must be deleted.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpRowLastChange.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpRowLastChange
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpRowLastChange.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpRowLastChange indicates the last time a successful set was performed on this row of the tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTable.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpDescription.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpDescription
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpDescription.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpDescription specifies the description of the ISA-AA group.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpAdminState.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpAdminState
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpAdminState.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpAdminState specifies the administrative state for the ISA-AA group. When 'outOfService', traffic destined to this ISA-AA group will apply its' tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFailToMode behaviour.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpOperState.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpOperState
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpOperState.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpOperState indicates the operational state for the ISA-AA group. When 'outOfService', traffic destined to this ISA-AA group will apply its' tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFailToMode behaviour.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFailToMode.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFailToMode
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFailToMode.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFailToMode specifies the operation upon failure of the group: is traffic to be permitted by setting to 'failToWire' or is it to be denied by setting to 'failToOpen'

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubPool.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubPool
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubPool.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubPool specifies the buffer pool as defined in TIMETRA-PORT-MIB::tmnxObjectAppPool for subscriber to network traffic egressing towards the ISA-AA MDA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubResvCbs.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubResvCbs
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubResvCbs.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubResvCbs specifies the percentage of the buffer pool reserved for high priority traffic for subscriber to network traffic egressing towards the ISA-AA MDA. The value '-1' implies that the reserved CBS should be computed as the sum of the CBS requested by the entities using this pool.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubSlpPolicy.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubSlpPolicy
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubSlpPolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubSlpPolicy specifies the policy as defined in TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tSlopePolicyTable for subscriber to network traffic egressing towards the ISA-AA MDA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubQuePolicy.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubQuePolicy
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubQuePolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubQuePolicy specifies the policy as defined in TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tNetworkQueueTable for subscriber to network traffic egressing towards the ISA-AA MDA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubSchPolicy.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubSchPolicy
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubSchPolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubSchPolicy specifies the policy as defined in TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tSchedulerPolicyTable for subscriber to network traffic egressing towards the ISA-AA MDA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubPool.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubPool
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubPool.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubPool specifies the buffer pool as defined in TIMETRA-PORT-MIB::tmnxObjectAppPool for network to subscriber traffic egressing towards the ISA-AA MDA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubResvCbs.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubResvCbs
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubResvCbs.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubResvCbs specifies the percentage of the buffer pool reserved for high priority traffic for network to subscriber traffic egressing towards the ISA-AA MDA. The value '-1' implies that the reserved CBS should be computed as the sum of the CBS requested by the entities using this pool.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubSlpPolicy.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubSlpPolicy
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubSlpPolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubSlpPolicy specifies the policy as defined in TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tSlopePolicyTable for network to subscriber traffic egressing towards the ISA-AA MDA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubQuePolicy.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubQuePolicy
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubQuePolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubQuePolicy specifies the policy as defined in TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tNetworkQueueTable for network to subscriber traffic egressing towards the ISA-AA MDA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubSchPolicy.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubSchPolicy
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubSchPolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubSchPolicy specifies the policy as defined in TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tSchedulerPolicyTable for network to subscriber traffic egressing towards the ISA-AA MDA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressPool.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressPool
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressPool.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressPool specifies the buffer pool as defined in TIMETRA-PORT-MIB::tmnxObjectAppPool for all traffic ingressing from the ISA-AA MDA. This object was obsoleted in release 7.0 and replaced with the TIMETRA-PORT-MIB::tmnxObjectAppPool object in the TIMETRA-PORT-MIB::tmnxQosPoolAppTable.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressResvCbs.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressResvCbs
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressResvCbs.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressResvCbs specifies the percentage of the buffer pool reserved for high priority traffic for all traffic ingressing from the ISA-AA MDA. The value '-1' implies that the reserved CBS should be computed as the sum of the CBS requested by the entities using this pool. This object was obsoleted in release 7.0 and replaced with the TIMETRA-PORT-MIB::tmnxObjectAppResvCbs object in the TIMETRA-PORT-MIB::tmnxQosPoolAppTable.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressSlpPolicy.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressSlpPolicy
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressSlpPolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressSlpPolicy specifies the policy as defined in TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tSlopePolicyTable for all traffic ingressing from the ISA-AA MDA. This object was obsoleted in release 7.0 and replaced with the TIMETRA-PORT-MIB::tmnxObjectAppSlopePolicy in the TIMETRA-PORT-MIB::tmnxQosPoolAppTable.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressQuePolicy.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressQuePolicy
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressQuePolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressQuePolicy specifies the policy as defined in TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tNetworkQueueTable for all traffic ingressing from the ISA-AA MDA. This object was obsoleted in release 7.0 and replaced with the TIMETRA-CHASSIS-MIB::tmnxMDANetworkIngQueues in the TIMETRA-CHASSIS-MIB::tmnxMDATable.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpActivityChange.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpActivityChange
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpActivityChange.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpActivityChange indicates the last time the value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaActivityState changed to or from 'active (1)' state for an ISA-AA MDA within the group.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpPartitions.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpPartitions
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpPartitions.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpPartitions specifies whether partitions are enabled or not within an ISA-AA group. When the value of this object is set to 'enabled', partitions can be created in the tmnxBsxAaGrpPartTable.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpCapCostLowThres.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpCapCostLowThres
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpCapCostLowThres.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpCapCostLowThres specifies the capacity cost low threshold for the ISA-AA group.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpCapCostHighThres.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpCapCostHighThres
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpCapCostHighThres.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpCapCostHighThres specifies the capacity cost high threshold for the ISA-AA group.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpLoadBalanceStatus.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpLoadBalanceStatus
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpLoadBalanceStatus.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpLoadBalanceStatus indicates the status of the load-balance operation for the ISA-AA group.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedEsmSubs.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedEsmSubs
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedEsmSubs.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedEsmSubs indicates the number of Enhanced Subscriber Management (ESM) subscribers that have not been assigned to an ISA-AA MDA within a group.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedSapSubs.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedSapSubs
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedSapSubs.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedSapSubs indicates the number of Service Access Point (SAP) subscribers that have not been assigned to an ISA-AA MDA within a group.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedSpkSubs.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedSpkSubs
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedSpkSubs.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedSpkSubs indicates the number of Spoke SDP subscribers that have not been assigned to an ISA-AA MDA within a group.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedTIpSubs.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedTIpSubs
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedTIpSubs.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpUnassignedTIpSubs indicates the number of Transit IP subscribers that have not been assigned to an ISA-AA MDA within a group. This object was obsoleted in release 9.0 and replaced with tmnxBsxIsaLoadBalUnSubTransit.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpAaSubScale.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpAaSubScale
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpAaSubScale.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpAaSubScale specifies the set of scaling limits that are supported with regards to the maximum number of AA subscribers per ISA and the corresponding policies that can be specified. The scaling limits may be one of: residential (0) - scaling limits for residential operation vpn (1) - scaling limits for VPNs mobileGateway (2) - scaling limits for operation as a mobile gateway tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpAaSubScale can only be set during row creation.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpOverloadCutThru.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpOverloadCutThru
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpOverloadCutThru.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpOverloadCutThru specifies whether or not overload cut-through is enabled. If enabled and an ISA overloads, all traffic is cut-through with no application identification or application specific policies applied until the ISA is no longer overloaded. Statistics are counter per subscriber against the cut-through protocol. If disabled and an ISA overloads, no action is taken.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfHiWmk.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfHiWmk
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfHiWmk.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfHiWmk specifies the high watermark for the weighted average utilization of the shared buffer space in the 'FromSub' buffer pool for each ISA. When a buffer pool is not in the overload state and the wa-shared buffer utilization for an ISA is greater than or equal to tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfHiWmk the ISA 'FromSub' buffer pool enters an overload state and an overload notification tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFmSbWaSBufOvld is raised. The value must be greater than tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfLoWmk. The value of -1 represents the maximum wa-shared buffer utilization indicating this high watermark will not be met.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfLoWmk.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfLoWmk
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfLoWmk.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfLoWmk specifies the low watermark for the weighted average utilization of the shared buffer space in the 'FromSub' buffer pool. When a buffer pool is in an overloaded state and the wa-shared buffer utilization for an ISA is less than or equal to tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfLoWmk the ISA 'FromSub' buffer pool leaves the overload state and a notification tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFmSbWaSBufOvldClr is sent to indicate the overload state has cleared. The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfLoWmk must be less than tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubWaSBfHiWmk.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfHiWmk.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfHiWmk
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfHiWmk.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfHiWmk specifies the high watermark for the weighed average utilization of the shared buffer space in the 'ToSub' buffer pool for each ISA. When a buffer pool is not in the overload state and the wa-shared buffer utilization for an ISA is greater than or equal to tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfHiWmk the ISA 'ToSub' buffer pool enters an overload state and an overload notification tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSbWaSBufOvld is raised. The value must be greater than tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfLoWmk. The value of -1 represents the maximum wa-shared buffer utilization indicating this high watermark will not be met.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfLoWmk.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfLoWmk
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfLoWmk.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfLoWmk specifies the low watermark for the weighted average utilization of the shared buffer space in the 'ToSub' buffer pool. When a buffer pool is in an overloaded state and the wa-shared buffer utilization for an ISA is less than or equal to tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfLoWmk the ISA 'ToSub' buffer pool leaves the overload state and a notification tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSbWaSBufOvldClr is sent to indicate the overload state has cleared. The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfLoWmk must be less than tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubWaSBfHiWmk.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV4NmEntr.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV4NmEntr
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV4NmEntr.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV4NmEntr specifies the number of transit prefix IPv4 entries to be supported on the ISA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV6NmEntr.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV6NmEntr
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV6NmEntr.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV6NmEntr specifies the number of transit prefix IPv6 entries to be supported on the ISA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV6RmEntr.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV6RmEntr
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV6RmEntr.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpTransPrefV6RmEntr specifies the number of remote transit prefix IPv6 entries to be supported on the ISA.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcTable.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcTable
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcTable.description: The tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcTable contains an entry for each divertable forwarding class for each BSX MDA Group in the system.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcEntry.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcEntry
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcEntry.description: Each tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcEntry indicates a divertable forwarding class for each BSX MDA Group in the system.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcRowStatus.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcRowStatus
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcRowStatus specifies the row status. It allows entries to be created and deleted in the tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcTable.

tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcRowLastChange.name: tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcRowLastChange
tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcRowLastChange.description: The value of tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcRowLastChange indicates the last time a successful set was performed on this row of the tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFcTable.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaTable.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaTable
tmnxBsxGrpMdaTable.description: The tmnxBsxGrpMdaTable contains an entry for each ISA-AA MDA configured within a group. This table is populated when an MDA is configured with an MDA type of ISA-AA, and associated with an ISA-AA group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaEntry.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaEntry
tmnxBsxGrpMdaEntry.description: Each tmnxBsxGrpMdaEntry indicates a ISA-AA MDA is associated to a tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpEntry.

tmnxBsxCardSlotNum.name: tmnxBsxCardSlotNum
tmnxBsxCardSlotNum.description: The value of tmnxBsxCardSlotNum indicates the slot number of this ISA-AA MDA.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaRowStatus.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaRowStatus
tmnxBsxGrpMdaRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaRowStatus specifies the row status. It allows entries to be created and deleted in the tmnxBsxGrpMdaTable. Rows are created by specifying the value of 'createAndGo (4)', and deleted by specifying the value of 'destroy (6)'.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaRowLastChange.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaRowLastChange
tmnxBsxGrpMdaRowLastChange.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaRowLastChange indicates the last time a successful set was performed on this row of the tmnxBsxGrpMdaTable.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaRole.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaRole
tmnxBsxGrpMdaRole.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaRole specifies the role of the MDA in the tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpEntry. The role can only be set at row creation, and cannot be modified.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaActivityState.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaActivityState
tmnxBsxGrpMdaActivityState.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaActivityState indicates the current activity status of the MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaActivityChange.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaActivityChange
tmnxBsxGrpMdaActivityChange.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaActivityChange indicates the last time the value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaActivityState changed to or from 'active (1)' or 'standby (2)' state for an ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaEsmSubscribers.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaEsmSubscribers
tmnxBsxGrpMdaEsmSubscribers.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaEsmSubscribers indicates the current number of Enhanced Subscriber Management (ESM) subscribers active on the ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaSapSubscribers.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaSapSubscribers
tmnxBsxGrpMdaSapSubscribers.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaSapSubscribers indicates the current number of Service Access Point (SAP) subscribers active on the ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaSpokeSdpSubscribers.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaSpokeSdpSubscribers
tmnxBsxGrpMdaSpokeSdpSubscribers.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaSpokeSdpSubscribers indicates the current number of Spoke SDP subscribers active on the ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaCapacityCost.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaCapacityCost
tmnxBsxGrpMdaCapacityCost.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaCapacityCost indicates the current capacity cost assigned to the ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaStatsResourceCount.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaStatsResourceCount
tmnxBsxGrpMdaStatsResourceCount.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaStatsResourceCount indicates the current number of Application Assurance subscriber statistics resources in use on the ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitIpSubs.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitIpSubs
tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitIpSubs.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitIpSubs indicates the current number of Transit IP subscribers active on the ISA-AA MDA in the group. This object will be obsolete in a future release in favour of tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitSubs.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitIpAddrs.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitIpAddrs
tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitIpAddrs.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitIpAddrs indicates the current number of Transit IP subscriber addresses associated with the ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitSubs.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitSubs
tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitSubs.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransitSubs indicates the current number of transit subscribers active on the ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefEntries.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefEntries
tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefEntries.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefEntries indicates the current number of transit prefix entries active on the ISA-AA MDA in the group. This object was obsoleted in release 10.0 and replaced with tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV4Entr for IPv4 entries along with tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV6Entr for IPv6 entries.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV4Entr.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV4Entr
tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV4Entr.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV4Entr indicates the current number of transit prefix IPv4 entries active on the ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV6Entr.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV6Entr
tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV6Entr.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV6Entr indicates the current number of transit prefix IPv6 entries active on the ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV6RemEntr.name: tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV6RemEntr
tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV6RemEntr.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpMdaTransPrefV6RemEntr indicates the current number of transit prefix IPv6 remote entries active on the ISA-AA MDA in the group.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusTable.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusTable
tmnxBsxGrpStatusTable.description: The tmnxBsxGrpStatusTable contains an entry for each ISA-AA MDA and Group in the system. Each row contains the performance-oriented status information per group for an ISA-AA MDA uniquely identified by the tmnxChassisIndex, tmnxBsxCardSlotNum, and the tmnxMDASlotNum.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEntry.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEntry
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEntry.description: Each tmnxBsxGrpStatusEntry contains the performance-oriented status information for a particular group and ISA-AA MDA. An index with a valid tmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex, tmnxChassisIndex set to one, and a zero value for each of the tmnxBsxCardSlotNum/tmnxMDASlotNum indices will return the summarized per group status. Rows in this table are created by the agent at initialization and cannot be created or destroyed by SNMP Set requests.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusDiscontTime.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusDiscontTime
tmnxBsxGrpStatusDiscontTime.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusDiscontTime indicates the SNMPv2-MIB::sysUpTime (hundredths of a second) when the ISA-AA MDA within the group has last changed status.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsIn.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsIn
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsIn.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsIn indicates the number of bytes diverted from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsIn.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsIn
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsIn.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsIn indicates the number of packets diverted from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInPChipErs.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInPChipErs
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInPChipErs.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInPChipErs indicates the number of packets discarded by the egress P-chip due to errors in the packets.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscCongIn.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscCongIn
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscCongIn.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscCongIn indicates the number of bytes discarded by the IOMs prior to the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to egress IOM congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscCongIn.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscCongIn
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscCongIn.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscCongIn indicates the number of packets discarded by the IOMs prior to the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to egress IOM congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsToMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsToMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsToMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsToMda indicates the number of bytes sent from an IOM towards the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsToMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsToMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsToMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsToMda indicates the number of packets sent from an IOM towards the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDisCongMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDisCongMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDisCongMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDisCongMda indicates the number of bytes discarded by the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDisCongMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDisCongMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDisCongMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDisCongMda indicates the number of packets discarded by the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscErrors.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscErrors
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscErrors.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscErrors indicates the number of bytes discarded due to unrecoverable errors.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscErrors.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscErrors
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscErrors.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscErrors indicates the number of packets discarded due to unrecoverable errors.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsPolicyByps.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsPolicyByps
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsPolicyByps.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsPolicyByps indicates the number of bytes passed untouched that did not have statistics or policy applied.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsPolicyByps.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsPolicyByps
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsPolicyByps.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsPolicyByps indicates the number of packets passed untouched that did not have statistics or policy applied.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsInspected.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsInspected
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsInspected.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsInspected indicates the number of bytes sent for protocol determination by the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInspected.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInspected
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInspected.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInspected indicates the number of packets sent for protocol determination by the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscPolicy.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscPolicy
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscPolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDiscPolicy indicates the number of bytes discarded by the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to policy.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscPolicy.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscPolicy
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscPolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDiscPolicy indicates the number of packets discarded by the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to policy.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsInMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsInMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsInMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsInMda indicates the number of bytes buffered by the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsInMda indicates the number of packets buffered by the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsFromMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsFromMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsFromMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsFromMda indicates the number of bytes sent from the ISA-AA MDA(s) to the local IOM.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsFromMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsFromMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsFromMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsFromMda indicates the number of packets sent from the ISA-AA MDA(s) to the local IOM.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsOutPChipEr.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsOutPChipEr
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsOutPChipEr.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsOutPChipEr indicates the number of packets discarded by the ingress P-chip due to errors in the packets.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDisCongOut.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDisCongOut
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDisCongOut.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsDisCongOut indicates the number of bytes discarded by the IOMs after the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to ingress IOM congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDisCongOut.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDisCongOut
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDisCongOut.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsDisCongOut indicates the number of packets discarded by the IOMs after the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to ingress IOM congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsOut.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsOut
tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsOut.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusOctsOut indicates the number of bytes sent to egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsOut.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsOut
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsOut.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktsOut indicates the number of packets sent to egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlows.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlows
tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlows.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlows indicates the total number of flows created on the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsCurrent.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsCurrent
tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsCurrent.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsCurrent indicates the number of flows currently being tracked by the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRate.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRate
tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRate.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRate indicates the number of flow setups per second. The calculation is weighted to give half of the weight to flows setup within the last five minutes and 25% weighting to flows setup in the previous five minutes, etc.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDiverted.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDiverted
tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDiverted.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDiverted indicates the number of subscribers defined in TIMETRA-SUBSCRIBER-MGMT-MIB::tmnxSubInfoAppProfile in the tmnxSubscriberInfoTable with tmnxBsxAppProfDivert set to 'true'.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsCurrent.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsCurrent
tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsCurrent.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsCurrent indicates the number of subscribers currently with flow records in the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRate.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRate
tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRate.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRate indicates the traffic rate in kilo-bits per second (kbps) incoming to the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsIn.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsIn
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsIn.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsIn indicates the number of bytes diverted from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsIn.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsIn
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsIn.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsIn indicates the number of packets diverted from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInPChipErs.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInPChipErs
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInPChipErs.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInPChipErs indicates the number of packets discarded by the egress P-chip due to errors in the packets.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDiscCongIn.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDiscCongIn

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscCongIn.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscCongIn
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscCongIn.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscCongIn indicates the number of packets discarded by the IOMs prior to the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to egress IOM congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsToMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsToMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsToMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsToMda indicates the number of bytes sent from an IOM towards the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsToMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsToMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsToMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsToMda indicates the number of packets sent from an IOM towards the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDisCongMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDisCongMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDisCongMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDisCongMda indicates the number of bytes discarded by the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDisCongMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDisCongMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDisCongMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDisCongMda indicates the number of packets discarded by the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDiscErrors.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDiscErrors
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDiscErrors.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDiscErrors indicates the number of bytes discarded due to unrecoverable errors.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscErrors.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscErrors
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscErrors.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscErrors indicates the number of packets discarded due to unrecoverable errors.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsPolicyByps.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsPolicyByps
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsPolicyByps.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsPolicyByps indicates the number of bytes passed untouched that did not have statistics or policy applied.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsPolicyByps.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsPolicyByps
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsPolicyByps.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsPolicyByps indicates the number of packets passed untouched that did not have statistics or policy applied.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsInspected.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsInspected
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsInspected.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsInspected indicates the number of bytes sent for protocol determination by the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInspected.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInspected
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInspected.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInspected indicates the number of packets sent for protocol determination by the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDiscPolicy.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDiscPolicy
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDiscPolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDiscPolicy indicates the number of bytes discarded by the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to policy policers or discard actions.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscPolicy.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscPolicy
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscPolicy.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDiscPolicy indicates the number of packets discarded by the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to policy policers or discard actions.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsInMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsInMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsInMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsInMda indicates the number of bytes buffered by the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsInMda indicates the number of packets buffered by the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsFromMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsFromMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsFromMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsFromMda indicates the number of bytes sent from the ISA-AA MDA(s) to the local IOM.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsFromMda.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsFromMda
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsFromMda.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsFromMda indicates the number of packets sent from the ISA-AA MDA(s) to the local IOM.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDisCongOut.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDisCongOut
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDisCongOut.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsDisCongOut indicates the number of bytes discarded by the IOMs after the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to ingress IOM congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDisCongOut.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDisCongOut
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDisCongOut.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsDisCongOut indicates the number of packets discarded by the IOMs after the ISA-AA MDA(s) due to ingress IOM congestion.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsOut.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsOut
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsOut.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCOctsOut indicates the number of bytes sent to egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsOut.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsOut
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsOut.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktsOut indicates the number of packets sent to egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCFlows.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCFlows
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCFlows.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCFlows indicates the number of flows seen by the ISA-AA MDA(s). Note that if the same 5-tuple is seen for a different flow within the flow timeout, it will still be considered one flow.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsAverage.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsAverage
tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsAverage.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsAverage indicates the average number of flows being tracked by the ISA-AA MDA(s) within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsPeak.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsPeak
tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsPeak.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowsPeak indicates the peak number of flows being tracked by the ISA-AA MDA(s) within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRateAvg.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRateAvg
tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRateAvg.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRateAvg indicates the average number of flow setups per second being tracked by the ISA-AA MDA(s) within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRatePk.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRatePk
tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRatePk.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowSetupRatePk indicates the peak number of flow setups per second being tracked by the ISA-AA MDA(s) within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDivertedAvg.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDivertedAvg
tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDivertedAvg.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDivertedAvg indicates the average number of subscribers defined in TIMETRA-SUBSCRIBER-MGMT-MIB::tmnxSubInfoAppProfile in the tmnxSubscriberInfoTable with tmnxBsxAppProfDivert set to 'true' within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDivertedPk.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDivertedPk
tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDivertedPk.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsDivertedPk indicates the peak number of subscribers defined in TIMETRA-SUBSCRIBER-MGMT-MIB::tmnxSubInfoAppProfile in the tmnxSubscriberInfoTable with tmnxBsxAppProfDivert set to 'true' within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsAverage.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsAverage
tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsAverage.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsAverage indicates the average number of subscribers with flow records in the ISA-AA MDA(s) within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsPeak.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsPeak
tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsPeak.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusSubsPeak indicates the peak number of subscribers with flow records in the ISA-AA MDA(s) within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRateAvg.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRateAvg
tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRateAvg.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRateAvg indicates the average traffic rate in kilo-bits per second (kbps) incoming to the ISA-AA MDA(s) within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRatePeak.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRatePeak
tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRatePeak.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusTrafficRatePeak indicates the peak traffic rate in kilo-bits per second (kbps) incoming to the ISA-AA MDA(s) within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRate.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRate
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRate.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRate indicates the current number of packets per second incoming to the ISA-AA MDA(s).

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRateAvg.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRateAvg
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRateAvg.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRateAvg indicates the average number of packets per second incoming to the ISA-AA MDA(s) within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRatePeak.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRatePeak
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRatePeak.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPacketRatePeak indicates the peak number of packets per second incoming to the ISA-AA MDA(s) within the last 60 minutes.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowResInUse.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowResInUse
tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowResInUse.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusFlowResInUse indicates the number of flow resources currently in-use on the ISA-AA MDA.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncPk.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncPk
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncPk.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncPk indicates the number of packets that the ISA-AA MDA has increased in size.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncPkLo.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncPkLo
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncPkLo.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncPkLo indicates the lower 32-bits of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncPk.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncPkHi.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncPkHi
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncPkHi.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncPkHi indicates the upper 32-bits of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncPk.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecPk.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecPk
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecPk.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecPk indicates the number of packets that the ISA-AA MDA has decreased in size.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecPkLo.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecPkLo
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecPkLo.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecPkLo indicates the lower 32-bits of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecPk.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecPkHi.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecPkHi
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecPkHi.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecPkHi indicates the upper 32-bits of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecPk.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncOc.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncOc
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncOc.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncOc indicates the total number of additional octets the ISA-AA MDA injected into the packets.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncOcLo.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncOcLo
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncOcLo.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncOcLo indicates the lower 32-bits of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncOcLo.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncOcHi.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncOcHi
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncOcHi.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzIncOcHi indicates the upper 32-bits of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzIncOc.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecOc.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecOc
tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecOc.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecOc indicates the total number of octets the ISA-AA MDA has removed from packets.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecOcLo.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecOcLo
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecOcLo.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecOcLo indicates the lower 32-bits of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecOc.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecOcHi.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecOcHi
tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecOcHi.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusPktSzDecOcHi indicates the upper 32-bits of tmnxBsxGrpStatusHCPktSzDecOc.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQTable.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQTable
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQTable.description: The tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQTable contains an entry for each ISA-AA MDA and Group in the system. Each row contains the Qos status information for traffic exiting an ISA-AA MDA given the tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQDirection and tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQIndex. An ISA-AA MDA is uniquely identified by the tmnxChassisIndex, tmnxBsxCardSlotNum, and the tmnxMDASlotNum.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQEntry.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQEntry
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQEntry.description: Each tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQEntry contains the Qos status information for traffic exiting a particular ISA-AA MDA within a group, given a tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQDirection and tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQIndex.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQDirection.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQDirection
tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQDirection.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQDirection specifies either the subscriber to network 'sub2net' or network to subscriber 'net2sub' direction of traffic. The value 'both' is not a valid index.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQIndex.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQIndex
tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQIndex.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusInQIndex specifies the number of the ingress queue as configured within the tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpIngressQuePolicy configured against this tmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDiscontTime.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDiscontTime
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDiscontTime.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDiscontTime indicates the SNMPv2-MIB::sysUpTime (hundredths of a second) when the ISA-AA MDA within this group has last changed status.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdInPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdInPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdInPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdInPPkts indicates the number of in profile packets diverted towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdOutPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdOutPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdOutPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdOutPPkts indicates the number of out of profile packets diverted towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdInPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdInPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdInPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdInPOcts indicates the number of in profile bytes diverted towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdOutPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdOutPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdOutPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQFwdOutPOcts indicates the number of out of profile bytes diverted towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroInPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroInPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroInPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroInPPkts indicates the number of in profile packets discarded towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroOutPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroOutPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroOutPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroOutPPkts indicates the number of out of profile packets discarded towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroInPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroInPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroInPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroInPOcts indicates the number of in profile bytes discarded towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroOutPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroOutPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroOutPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQDroOutPOcts indicates the number of out of profile bytes discarded towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdInPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdInPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdInPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdInPPkts indicates the number of in profile packets diverted towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdOutPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdOutPPkts

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdInPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdInPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdInPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdInPOcts indicates the number of in profile bytes diverted towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdOutPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdOutPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdOutPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCFwdOutPOcts indicates the number of out of profile bytes diverted towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroInPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroInPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroInPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroInPPkts indicates the number of in profile packets discarded towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroOutPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroOutPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroOutPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroOutPPkts indicates the number of out of profile packets discarded towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroInPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroInPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroInPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroInPOcts indicates the number of in profile bytes discarded towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroOutPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroOutPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroOutPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusIngQHCDroOutPOcts indicates the number of out of profile bytes discarded towards egress IOMs from the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQTable.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQTable
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQTable.description: The tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQTable contains an entry for each ISA-AA MDA and Group in the system. Each row contains the Qos status information for traffic entering an ISA-AA MDA given the tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDirection and tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQIndex. An ISA-AA MDA is uniquely identified by the tmnxChassisIndex, tmnxBsxCardSlotNum, and the tmnxMDASlotNum.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQEntry.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQEntry
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQEntry.description: Each tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQEntry contains the Qos status information for traffic incoming to a particular ISA-AA MDA within a group, given a tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDirection and tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQIndex.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDirection.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDirection
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDirection.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDirection specifies either the subscriber to network 'sub2net' or network to subscriber 'net2sub' direction of traffic. The value 'both' is not a valid index.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQIndex.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQIndex
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQIndex.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQIndex specifies the number of the egress queue as configured within the tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpToSubQuePolicy or tmnxBsxIsaAaGrpFromSubQuePolicy configured against this tmnxBsxIsaAaGroupIndex.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDiscontTime.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDiscontTime
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDiscontTime.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDiscontTime indicates the SNMPv2-MIB::sysUpTime (hundredths of a second) when the ISA-AA MDA within the group has last changed status.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdInPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdInPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdInPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdInPPkts indicates the number of in profile packets diverted from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdOutPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdOutPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdOutPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdOutPPkts indicates the number of out of profile packets diverted from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdInPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdInPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdInPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdInPOcts indicates the number of in profile bytes diverted from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdOutPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdOutPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdOutPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQFwdOutPOcts indicates the number of out of profile bytes diverted from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroInPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroInPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroInPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroInPPkts indicates the number of in profile packets discarded from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroOutPPkts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroOutPPkts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroOutPPkts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroOutPPkts indicates the number of out of profile packets discarded from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.

tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroInPOcts.name: tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroInPOcts
tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroInPOcts.description: The value of tmnxBsxGrpStatusEgrQDroInPOcts indicates the number of in profile bytes discarded from ingress IOMs towards the ISA-AA MDA within this group for the particular queue.
